cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.SC 

The paper deals with the problem of computing numerical invariants of programs using abstract interpretation and linear constraint domains. This falls under the category of program analysis and verification, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. "cs.LO" (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal methods and fixpoint computations. "cs.PL" (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with program analysis. "cs.SE" (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper deals with static analysis techniques for software. "cs.FL" (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also possible as the paper deals with formal methods and transition relations. "cs.SC" (Symbolic Computation) is another possible category as the paper deals with quantifier elimination and linear real arithmetic formulas.
